avors, adhering to formula guidelines, regulations and scale-up procedures Use their knowledge of raw materials and recipes to rapidly and efficiently duplicate competitor products in accordance with project parameters and customer requirements To apply sensory & analytical understanding and techniques into product evaluations interpreting the results and feeding them back to the project team with recommendations for next steps To undertake raw material & product stability trials, using a range of analytical methodologies and report the results back to the Technical team To support the Operations team when there are quality issues with the raw materials, processing or finished products To contribute to the local, regional and global product libraries ensuring information is accurate, up-to-date and readily available. Skills & Abilities Good people and communication skills, with written and oral English a must Ability to work within short time-frames Capability to stay focused under pressure and translate results directly into new products which meet our customer\u2019s requirements Education & Experience A Bachelor's degree (or equivalent) in Chemistry or Food Science/Technology A minimum 3 years of Flavor creation experience in the food industry About Sensient Flavors & Fragrances Sensient Flavors & Fragrances Group develops, manufactures and distributes flavor and fragrance systems that are found in thousands of consumer products worldwide. The company's specialty systems are essential components of food, beverage, household and personal care products. Sensient's value-added flavors and fragrances enable our customers to excel in highly competitive global markets. The Flavors & Fragrances Group is located in Hoffman Estates, Illinois. About Sensient Technologies Corporation Sensient Technologies Corporation is a leading global manufacturer and marketer of colors, flavors, and fragrances. Sensient employs advanced technologies at facilities around the world to develop specialty food and beverage systems, cosmetic and pharmaceutical systems, inkjet and specialty inks and colors, and other specialty and fine chemicals. The Company's customers include major international manufacturers representing most of the world's best-known brands. Sensient is headquartered in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. As a dynamic and diversified global leader, we offer an excellent salary and comprehensive benefits package. For more information, visit our website at http://www.sensient.com Equal Opportunity Employer Primary Location: Europe, Middle East and Africa-South Africa-Gauteng-Sandton Work Locations: South Africa Sandton Office 11 Mastiff Rd., Long Lake Ext 1 Linbro Business Park Sandton 1608 Job: Research and Development Organization: Food Colors South Africa Schedule: Full-time Shift: Day/Shift 1 Employee Status: Regular Job Type: Standard Job Posting: May 27, 2020, 8:40:22 AM Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
